children.label: testId
description: Returns `data-test-subj` of button group

children.label: getElement
description: Returns button group element if found, otherwise `null`.

children.label: getOptions
description:
Returns all options of button groups.
Returns empty array if button group is not found.

children.label: getSelected
description: Returns selected option of button group, or `null` if none is selected or button group is not found.

children.label: select
description: Select option from group

children.label: #containerEl
description: Returns combobox container or throws

children.label: #inputEl
description:
Returns the input element (role="combobox")
Finds it within or near the container

children.label: testId
description: Returns `data-test-subj` of combobox

children.label: getElement
description: Returns combobox container if found, otherwise `null`.

children.label: getSelected
description:
Returns selected values as array of strings.

Reads from pills with `data-test-subj="euiComboBoxPill"`.
Returns empty array if combobox is not found.

children.label: select
description:
Select an option by typing its label and pressing Enter

IMPORTANT: Must use the exact display label, not the internal value
Example: Use 'Semantic text' not 'semantic_text'

children.label: label
description: - The display label of the option to select

children.label: clear
description:
Clear all selected options and wait for the UI to settle.

Notes:
- Some EUI combobox usages render `comboBoxClearButton` outside of the element that carries the
  consumer-provided `data-test-subj` (e.g. on a wrapper). This method searches a broader scope.
- If the clear button is not available, it falls back to removing pills via Backspace.

classes.label: EuiContextMenuTestHarness
description:
Harness for context menus rendered inside EUI popovers.

Note: EUI context menu items may render as `<button>` or `<a>` depending on props.

children.label: getElement
description: Returns the popover panel element if it is still in the DOM, otherwise `null`.

children.label: getMenuItem
description:
Get a clickable context menu item (button or link) by its accessible name.
Returns `null` if not found.

classes.label: EuiListTestHarness
description:
Generic harness for EUI "list-ish" UIs (selectables, list groups, option lists) where:
- Items are rendered as repeated DOM nodes containing an item label text
- Row actions are rendered somewhere "near" the label (often not a strict parent/child relationship)

This harness encapsulates the common pattern:
- locate item by visible label text
- walk up a bounded number of ancestors until the action button is found
- click it

children.label: getElement
description: Returns list container element if found, otherwise `null`.

children.label: clickAction
description: Click an action button associated with an item label.

children.label: getActionElement
description:
Return the action element for an item label (bounded ancestor walk).
Exposed to enable assertions before clicking if needed.
Returns `null` if not found.

classes.label: EuiPaginationTestHarness
description:
Harness for EUI pagination (EuiPagination / EuiTablePagination).

Encapsulates the DOM details of locating pagination buttons.

classes.label: EuiPopoverPanelTestHarness
description:
Finder for EUI popover panels (`[data-popover-panel]`).

EuiPopoverPanel renders a stable `data-popover-panel` attribute (see EUI source).

This harness is intentionally discovery-focused and returns `HTMLElement`s and/or
other harness instances that operate on a specific panel.

children.label: currentCommonlyUsedRange
description:
This method returns the currently selected commonly-used range as a string

The empty string is returned if a commonly-used range is not currently selected

children.label: currentRange
description:
This method returns the currently selected range as a pair of strings.
Returns `null` if the date picker is not found or not properly initialized.

children.label: assertCurrentRange
description:
This method runs an assertion against the currently selected range using
UNIX timestamps.

NOTE: it does not (yet) support commonly-used (textual) ranges like "Last 15 minutes"
signature: (range: { from: number; to: number; }, expect: jest.Expect) => void

children.label: togglePopover
description: Opens the popover for the date picker

children.label: selectCommonlyUsedRange
description: Selects a commonly-used range from the date picker (opens the popover if it's not already open)

children.label: refresh
description: Activates the refresh button

children.label: #containerEl
description: Returns super select container or throws

children.label: #buttonEl
description:
Returns the button element that opens the dropdown.

Note: depending on how `data-test-subj` is applied, the element returned by
`getByTestId()` may itself be the `<button>` control (not a wrapper). In
that case `within(container).getByRole('button')` would fail because the
container has no descendants.

children.label: testId
description: Returns `data-test-subj` of super select

children.label: getElement
description: Returns super select element if found, otherwise `null`.

children.label: getSelected
description:
Preferred alias for selected option.
Returns empty string if super select is not found.

children.label: select
description: Select an option by opening the dropdown and clicking the option
signature: (optionTestSubj: string, options?: { allowMultiple?: boolean | undefined; index?: number | undefined; } | undefined) => Promise<void>

children.label: optionTestSubj
description: - The data-test-subj of the option to select

children.label: allowMultiple
description:
If multiple options match the same `data-test-subj`, set this to true and use `index`
to select a specific option.

children.label: index
description: Which matching option to click (defaults to 0). Only used when allowMultiple is true.

children.label: selectById
description:
Select an option by its DOM id (EUI often sets `id` on options to the option value).

Useful when options don't have stable/unique `data-test-subj`.

children.label: testId
description: Returns `data-test-subj` of table

children.label: getElement
description: Returns table element if found, otherwise `null`.

children.label: getBody
description: Returns the table body (`<tbody>`) if found, otherwise `null`.

children.label: getRows
description:
Get table row elements for direct interaction with cells.
Useful when you need to click buttons, checkboxes, or other interactive elements within rows.
returnComment: Array of table row elements (empty array if table/body not found)

children.label: getRowByCellText
description:
Find a row by visible text content in any cell.
Works for EUI tables rendered with semantic <tr>/<td>.
Returns `null` if the text is not found or not inside a table row.

children.label: getCellValues
description:
Get table cell values (tbody only) as a 2D array.

Defaults are geared towards typical test assertions (trimmed + whitespace-collapsed).
signature: (options?: { trim?: boolean | undefined; collapseWhitespace?: boolean | undefined; }) => string[][]

functions.label: getSelectedButtonInGroup
description: Helper function to get the selected button in a button group
